---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

// Services / Packages page.
//
// Per relay #37 §6: this page can be its own surface, but each
// package must feel "calmly available" — NO sales hierarchy,
// NO "best value," NO comparison aggression.
//
// Packages are presented as plain editorial blocks (<article>)
// with equal visual weight. Pricing is left optional — many
// concierge practices gate pricing behind the discovery call.
// Stacey can choose to surface or hide prices when she edits.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services"
  description="How Stacey works — the Discovery Call, what a session looks like, and the ways to work together."
>
  <!-- =====================================================
       Process clarity
       Demystifies before asking. Reads like a calm
       explanation, not a sales pitch.
       ===================================================== -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h1 id="process-heading">How Stacey works</h1>

      <p>
        Every working relationship starts the same way: with a Discovery
        Call. It's a short conversation, free, and no pressure to
        continue. Stacey listens, asks a few questions, and tells you
        honestly whether she can help.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you decide to keep going, sessions feel a lot like Grampy's
        kitchen table. We sit down, plain language, and look at three
        specific things together &mdash; the things that, once they're clear,
        tend to settle the rest of the picture.
      </p>

      <p>
        You leave a session with: a clearer picture of where you are,
        one or two concrete next steps you can actually do, and
        permission to stop worrying about the rest until next time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =====================================================
       Packages
       Editorial blocks, equal visual weight. NO badges.
       ===================================================== -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="packages-heading">
    <div class="column-wide">
      <h2 id="packages-heading">Ways to work together</h2>

      <p>
        These are the ways Stacey commonly works with people. None is
        better than another &mdash; they're shaped to fit different lives.
      </p>

      <article style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3>The Clarity Session</h3>
        <p>
          A single conversation, in depth. For people who want one
          good look at their picture &mdash; current accounts, income,
          obligations, hopes &mdash; and want to leave with one or two
          concrete next steps. No ongoing commitment.
        </p>
        <p class="caption">
          Single session. Pricing on the Discovery Call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3>The Quarterly Check-In</h3>
        <p>
          For people who'd rather not figure money out alone four times
          a year. We pick up where the last conversation left off, look
          at what's changed, and adjust. Useful for life that has more
          moving parts &mdash; couples, families, parents and aging parents,
          people in transition.
        </p>
        <p class="caption">
          Recurring quarterly. Pricing on the Discovery Call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3>The Family Conversation</h3>
        <p>
          For families who want to talk about money together &mdash; across
          generations, across couples, across siblings sorting out a
          parent's care. Stacey facilitates. The hard parts go better
          when there's someone steady at the table.
        </p>
        <p class="caption">
          Custom scope. Pricing on the Discovery Call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p style="margin-top: 4rem;">
        Not sure which fits? <a href="/contact">Book a Discovery Call</a>
        &mdash; that's what it's for.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =====================================================
       What this is NOT
       Quietly clarifies. Reduces fear of misunderstanding.
       ===================================================== -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="not-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h2 id="not-heading">What this isn't</h2>

      <p>
        Stacey isn't a financial advisor or a registered investment
        advisor. She doesn't sell investment products. She doesn't
        manage your accounts or take a percentage of your assets.
      </p>

      <p>
        She charges a flat fee for her time. That's it. The
        relationship is between her and you, not her and a broker.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
